race.description: Belle Property Hawkesbury CG&E Mdn Plate
race.comment: PATONGA (6) didn't have much luck in the first part of the race but managed to work home well for fifth on debut over 1200m at Kembla last start. Perfectly placed over an extra furlong. Drawn to advantage so everything points towards a big run. REIGN OF HONOR (7) progressed nicely last start when facing the starter for the second time, leading for home only to be edged out late over this trip at Kembla. Winning chance with further improvement on the cards. COYOTE (2) wound up in good style but was never a threat over 1300m here last time. Cherry ripe now and an extra 100m helps. ENGLISH CONQUEROR (4) has been close to the mark at his last couple and an extra 200m will suit.
